ovence, Alpes-de-Haute-Provence, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hanses","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Hanks  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): metronymic from the Yiddish female personal name <i>Khanke</i> (a pet form of <i>Khane</i>, from Hebrew <i>Ḥanna</i>; see   Hanna   6), with the Yiddish possessive suffix <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Hanks","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Hanke</i>, with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. In England this personal name was a shortened form of both   Hankin   and   Hancock  , both of which were used as pet forms of   Henry  . The equivalent Middle Dutch names <i>Hanke</i> and <i>Hankin</i>, however, had the sense ‘young John’ and may have been introduced to England by Flemish settlers after the Conquest. There is no evidence to support the suggestion that an English hereditary surname was formed from the Old Norse personal name <i>Anki</i>, a diminutive of personal names such as <i>Arngrim</i> and <i>Arnketill</i>."]}]},{"name":"Schroder","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Erwin, Kurt, Hans, Klaus, Darrold, Dietrich, Erna, Frieda, Gunther, Horst, Juergen, Otto.","North German (<b>Schröder</b>): see   Schroeder  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Schroeder","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Otto, Hans, Erwin, Fritz, Helmut, Horst, Alois, Ernst, Ewald, Gerhard, Klaus.","North German (mainly <b>Schröder</b>): occupational name for a cloth cutter or tailor, from an agent derivative of Middle Low German <i>schrōden</i>, <i>schrāden</i> ‘to cut’. The same term was occasionally used to denote a grist miller as well as a shoemaker, whose work included cutting leather, and also a drayman, one who delivered beer and wine in bulk to customers; in some instances the surname may have been acquired in either of these senses. This surname is also found France (Alsace and Lorraine) and Poland. Compare   Schroder  ."]}]},{"name":"Severus","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Nottinghamshire and Yorkshire): variant of   Severn  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Severn","meanings":["From the Roman family name <i>Severus</i> ‘stern, severe’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Severus Hanses Schroder was born in 1540 as the son of Hanses Schroder -. He married Gesche Schroder in 1560. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1592, in Allemagne-en-Provence, Alpes-de-Haute-Provence, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, France, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1540–1592":"1540–1592","1540–1590":"1540–1590","1560–1636":"1560–1636","1514–1611":"1514–1611","1514":"1514","1611":"1611","1540":"1540","1560":"1560","1592":"1592","1590":"1590","1636":"1636","Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Deutschland":"Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Germany, Allemagne, Alpes-de-Haute-Provence, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, France":"Allemagne-en-Provence, Alpes-de-Haute-Provence, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1540–1592":"1540–1592","1540–1590":"1540–1590","1560–1636":"1560–1636","1514–1611":"1514–1611","1514":"1514","1611":"1611","1540":"1540","1560":"1560","1592":"1592","1590":"1590","1636":"1636","Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Deutschland":"Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksa","Germany, Allemagne, Alpes-de-Haute-Provence, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, France":"Allemagne-en-Provence, Alpes-de-Haute-Provence, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, Ranska"},"fr":{"1540–1592":"1540–1592","1540–1590":"1540–1590","1560–1636":"1560–1636","1514–1611":"1514–1611","1514":"1514","1611":"1611","1540":"1540","1560